The Education Department in the Eastern Cape admits to a few hiccups leading up to the opening of schools in the province. eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports. #dstv403 EAST LONDON - The reopening of coastal schools has left some families in the Eastern Cape highly frustrated. Over 1,000 pupils still need to find places at schools across the province. READ: Back to school | Over 900 unplaced pupils in Western Cape But the education department says there's no need to panic, assuring parents that all children will be in class in the next two weeks. While most schools are off to a smooth start to the year, others face infrastructure-related problems. * eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports.